                <fr:uri>https://www.my-great-forest.net/schm-DF6J/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>schm-DF6J</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/schm-DF6J/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Finite schemes are affine">Finite schemes are affine</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
  As a corollary of <fr:link href="/schm-80MC/" title="A scheme is affine iff it is spectral" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/schm-80MC/" display-uri="schm-80MC" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/schm-80MC/" display-uri="schm-80MC" /></fr:link>, if a scheme <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is finite, then it is affine, since finite sober spaces are all spectral.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
